The paper focuses on computer vision algorithms for autonomous vehicles, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning and GANs also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The discussion of adversarial attacks suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the focus on autonomous vehicles suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
